						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Realising-Gender-in-Agricultural-Policies-The-Fight-for-Equality-is-not-Over2" title="Realising Gender in Agricultural Policies: The Fight for Equality is not Over" alt="link">Realising Gender in Agricultural Policies: The Fight for Equality is not Over</a></h2>

	
					<p> 
Rebecca Holmes and Rachel Slater, ODI Opinion 91, Overseas Development Institute, December 2007More than two decades separate two major World Development Reports on rural agriculture: 1982’s report on ‘Agriculture and Economic Development’ and the 2008 report ‘Agriculture for Development’. During this time, there has not only been a marked shift in the way in which the agricultural sector has been addressed within international policy, but there have been radical changes in the way that women’s roles in development, particularly in rural development and agriculture, have been perceived, analysed and addressed. This briefing addresses the barriers that women face in agriculture. The authors provide evidence that greater gender equality is likely to increase efficiency and productivity in the agricultural sector.  </p>
							<p><span class="date">18/01/2008</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Realising-Gender-in-Agricultural-Policies-The-Fight-for-Equality-is-not-Over2">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Poverty-in-Focus-Gender-Equality" title="Poverty in Focus: Gender Equality" alt="link">Poverty in Focus: Gender Equality</a></h2>

	
					<p> 
UNDP International Poverty Centre, January 2008This issue of Poverty in Focus presents a dozen articles on recent research results and commentaries on the links between gender and poverty. The issue notes that empowering women by improving their living conditions and enabling them to actively participate in the social and economic life of a country may be the key for long-term sustainable development.  </p>
							<p><span class="date">18/01/2008</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Poverty-in-Focus-Gender-Equality">Read more...</a>
